node.text: End of a crazy week. I bought a 2021 Ram TRX in Anchorage on Monday and proceeded to drive 2,000 miles through the muddiest terrain to the edge of America...to Deadhorse, Alaska with my mom. We could’ve flown to Hawaii first class, stayed at a 5 star hotel and ate steak every night for cheaper....guess I know who I get my sense of adventure from.

node.text: When my parents were married on August 22, 1981, they moved to Anchorage, Alaska where they spent their first two years of marriage.  They moved to Oregon, I was born and they never made it back to Alaska to visit.  Today, 40 years later, my Momma and I are on a flight to Anchorage to spend a week exploring.  Happy 40th anniversary Mom and Dad...we miss and love you Pops ❤️
